{
  "stem": "1343.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] We were talking about if we were able to find, because by that time, we had lice that eating us up alive.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the lice was the one that carried the typhoid fever, also.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And if-- and when we had strength, we were talking about food.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And everybody was allowed one story, so mine was always-- mine was the Friday nights and the Friday night menu.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Gefilte fish, chicken soup with matzo ball, chicken paprikash-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--and cake, and the challah that my mother made.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Everybody would talk about different meals they remembered?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We actually tormented each other-- [LAUGHTER] --because we were hungry, but it would be talking about food.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[SIGHS] We got bread, 12 of us, which was half of it sawdust, actually, [LAUGHS] we found out after, and one soup a day that was more liquid than anything else.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And whenever the distribution of the food was, also, it was such a chaos, such a tumult everywhere that, many times, the push was so hard that we turned over the soup, and people were [LAUGHS] licking it up like pigs from the [? sty. ?] And it's unbelievable, what human beings can be.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Not from Mauthausen, [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And in Mauthausen, we met another uncle of mine who came back from Russia in time to be deported to [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But he was still a strong, strapping six-footer, and he actually force-fed him.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Force-fed the other uncle?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Was that his brother?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And that uncle also got liberated, and he lives now in Israel.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And he's the one who actually saved my life, too, later on.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
